content:
To configure a messaging for web deployment:

Publish a deployment by creating and publishing a new embedded service deployment. This requires enabling digital experiences, creating a new deployment, selecting the conversation type as Messaging for In-App and Web, and naming the Embedded Service deployment.

Customize your deployment by editing settings, branding, pre-chat values, and copying code snippet to deliver conversations to your website. You can also add business hours, override business hours, use API to hide or show messaging button at specified times, and customize labels for fields and alt text in your messaging experience.

Add messaging to your website by installing the code snippet, selecting it, copying it, pasting it before the closing body tag, and ensuring that the header of the chat button page doesn't contain a referrer policy of no-referrer. Optionally, include the Meta Tag Code Snippet in the head element to make your page responsive to all devices.

Set security protocols for your deployment by adding your domain to the CORS allowlist, entering an origin URL pattern, and saving your work. This is required if using an external website, but not necessary for Experience Builder or Commerce Cloud sites.
title: Configuring Service Cloud Messaging for Web
